{
  "texts": [
    "Local regulations are envisioned as potential best-practice frameworks for global adoption, similar to privacy regulations.",
    "Within this imaginary, the U.S. and China are often represented as global counter-players in this AI race (DE1, DE7).",
    "\"Economic discourse on international competitiveness against China and the U.S. is becoming a reality right now (.",
    "with very oppositional takes on where to situate Germany between regulation and pioneering development\" (DE1).",
    "These oppositional takes revolve around the type and specificity of regulation needed, as AI is discussed as an umbrella term for automation technologies."
  ]
}